Quick Start Guide# Installation in 3 Steps# # 1. Clone with submodules git clone --recurse-submodules https://github.com/gotm-model/code.git cd code # 2. Configure and build cmake -G Ninja -B build -S . cmake --build build # 3. Install (optional) cmake --install build --prefix ~/.localRun Your First Test Case# # Clone test cases git clone --recurse-submodules https://github.com/gotm-model/cases.git cd cases/nns_annual # Run simulation gotm # Output: result.ncAnalyze Results# Using Python:
import netCDF4 as nc import matplotlib.pyplot as plt # Load data ds = nc.Dataset(&#39;result.nc&#39;) temp = ds.variables[&#39;temp&#39;][:] z = ds.variables[&#39;z&#39;][:] # Plot plt.contourf(temp.T, levels=20) plt.colorbar(label=&#39;Temperature (°C)&#39;) plt.show()Using command-line tools:
ncdump -h result.nc # View metadata ncview result.nc # Visual inspection (if installed)Next Steps# Explore test cases for more examples Learn about configuration options Understand the theory behind GOTM Read about modules for customization Getting Help# Browse documentation Check GitHub Issues Join GitHub Discussions
